  <div style="float:left; width:65%; font-size:91%"> <a name="content"></a>
    <h2><a href="training.asp">Tools</a> / 
      Guide to Keeping Healthy</h2>
    <p><img src="../images/Keeping_Healthy_After_the_Hospital.jpg" alt="Cover - Guide to Keeping Healthy" width="200" height="293" border="1" class="pic-right" />This manual introduces recovery and wellness to people experiencing a short psychiatric hospitalization. It is designed to be used in clinician- or peer-facilitated groups, or independently by consumers. It motivates users to take steps toward better physical health and wellness upon leaving the hospital. The manual's components include a guide for clinicians, the manual itself, and a pocket-sized portable health plan. </p>
    <p>Developed by the New York City Health and Hospitals Corporation, Office of Behavioral Health, it can be downloaded by clicking on the links below. Versions are available in English, Spanish, French, Polish, Russian, and Bengali.</p>
    <p>&nbsp;</p>
